FBIS4-66087 "drweu103__a94005" FBIS-WEU-94-103-A Daily Report 27 May 1994 ANNEX Inter-European Affairs EU Expresses `Grave' Concern for Situation in Crimea EU Expresses `Grave' Concern for Situation in Crimea BR2605143094 Brussels RAPID Database in English 26 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR2605143094 Brussels RAPID Database English BFN [EC Document No. DOC/PESC/94/52: "Communique on the Situation in Crimea"] [Text] The EU [European Union] expresses its grave concern at the recent developments in the Crimean region of Ukraine. Noting that the situation in the Crimea has deteriorated over the past week, and taking into consideration the decision of the Crimean Parliament of 20 May, it urges the continuation of efforts to find negotiated and legitimate solutions to the issue, without resort to confrontation or unilateral actions. The EU reaffirms its full support for the territorial integrity of a sovereign Ukraine in accordance with the charter of the United Nations and with the principles of the CSCE final act and warns against actions which risk creating instability in the area. The EU reiterates that an escalation of the conflict would have severe consequences for the stability in East Europe.
